Vice President Kamala Harris spoke with Dr. Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala, Director-General of the World Trade Organization, to offer support in addressing the economic and health consequences of COVID-19 and climate change. They discussed prioritizing resilience in the global supply chain and using trade to promote equity and economic growth. Reforms within the World Trade Organization were also mentioned to enhance its effectiveness. The Vice President emphasized the United States' focus on investing in health and technology for sustainable development. Both parties committed to working closely together to accelerate momentum in the global economy.